-- Yahoo says board to consider Microsoft offer
-- 
-- Fri Feb 1, 2008 8:58am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/01/us-yahoo-microsoft-yahoo-board-idUSWNAS898320080201

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Yahoo Inc confirmed on Friday that it had received an unsolicited bid from Microsoft Corp to acquire the company and that its board of directors would consider the $44.6 billion deal. 

 Yahoo said in a statement that its board would evaluate the proposal "carefully and promptly in the context of Yahoo's strategic plans and pursue the best course of action to maximize long-term value for shareholders." (Reporting by  Eric Auchard ; Editing by Jeffrey Benkoe)